%N A278180 Square spiral in which each new term is the sum of its two largest neighbors.
%C A278180 To evaluate a(n) consider the neighbors of a(n) that are present in the spiral when a(n) should be a new term in the spiral.
%C A278180 For the same idea but for a hexagonal spiral see A278619; and for a right triangle see A278645. It appears that the same idea for an isosceles triangle and also for a square array gives A030237. - _Omar E. Pol_, Dec 04 2016
